🇬🇧 When I started practicing jiujitsu I heard that purple belts were the hardest to get, 90% of people who start don't get there, I just got mine but let me tell you what it took.

In 2016 I started training at @fightsportsmiami 🇺🇸 under one of my all-time heroes @cyborgbjj, I was doing well and then broke my hand, an injury that still hurts everyday. Stopped for a while but in 2020 started training again at @graciebarramelrose in South Africa 🇿🇦under @yronkaironbjj, @iamjamesboston and @storm_89_conrad three super talented black belts. Less than a year into it my left meniscus was destroyed and had to go for surgery, out again for months. Went back in with debilitated knees and hamstrings (another old injury) and kept pushing. My meniscus tore again this year and had to take it easy for a while so we decided to do a private program of one on one lessons focused on technique and rolling. 

I wasn't expecting a promotion to purple belt since I didn't get much rolling time this year due to injuries but my coach felt I deserved it and I'm grateful for it. 

But then another heartbreaking moment came. The promotion ceremonies happened two days after we moved to Europe so as we were packing our bags and getting ready to go to the airport my coach @iamjamesboston stopped by our house and put the belt around my waist in our garden, not how I pictured it would happen but still a very special moment I'll never forget. It is an understatement to say that I've worked hard for that belt 💜

Thanks to our coaches, training partners and friends we've made through this journey, it's been hard but very rewarding, jiujitsu has taught me many lessons that I apply everyday in my life with my family and at my job, it has made me a better person and has taught me to be patient and to come back no matter what gets thrown at me. 

Excited to keep training and learning from it.
.
.

🇬🇧 I truly believe in the power of a good story, not only because they're fun to tell but because people remember them. 

I've used storytelling as a training technique for many years, from interns and students to directors and clients. This has helped me unlock many things in my professional journey.

Here are 5 simple differences between speaking as an expert and sharing experiences (to me, the foundation of good storytelling in my field):

- Experts focus on the great results they accomplish; experience storytellers share the journey.
- Experts make you think they're unbeatable, exp st. Don't mind showing vulnerability.
- Experts are a constant success story, exp st. make emphasis on the mistakes they made. 
- Experts are unrelatable, exp st. are familiar, an everyday person like you and me.
- Experts frame their story as an exclusive pack for a few, exp. st make sure they share for all. 

Follow and share experiences; they're easier to remember, emulate and ultimately implement.

Have an awesome week! 
.
.
🇪🇸 Siempre he creído en el poder de una buena historia, no sólo porque es divertido contarlas sino porque la gente las recuerda.

Yo he usado las historias para entrenar gente por muchos años, desde pasantes/interns hasta líderes y clientes. Esto me ha ayudado a desbloquear muchas cosas en mi camino profesional.

Aquí les comparto 5 diferencias entre hablar como experto y compartir experiencias (en esencia una de las bases para contar buenas historias en mi campo).

- Los expertos se enfocan en sus grandes resultados, los que comparten experiencias en el camino para lograrlos.
Los expertos se muestran como invencibles, los que comparten experiencias como seres vulnerables normales.
- Los expertos son una historia de éxito andante, los que comparten experiencias se enfocan en los errores cometidos.
- Los expertos son difícil de emular, como gente de otro mundo por encima de los demás, los otros son más familiares, gente del común.
- Los expertos empaquetan su conocimiento como si fuera para un selecto grupo, los otros se aseguran de que sea para todos.

¡Que tengan una gran semana! 
.
.

🇪🇸 Siempre he creído en el poder de las palabras y de manifestar lo que uno quiere para su vida. Poner esto en perspectiva y agregar un plan con esfuerzo realmente hace que lo que quieras pase. Este para mí fue un año de cambios y logros. Haber escrito Scribbles, moverme para Europa, mi cinturón morado en Jiujitsu, leer más, entre otras cosas fueron cosas que declaré el año pasado y trabajé duro para lograr. Debo también confesar que en algunas otras fallé, no tuve (o dediqué) el tiempo suficiente, pero está bien, es parte del proceso.

Quiero que hoy declaremos o manifestemos juntos las metas, cambios o logros que queremos para 2023 ¿Cuáles son los tuyos? También quiero que cuando sientas que necesitas recordarlos vengas a este mensaje y lo hagas, a veces esto nos hace falta a todos. Algunas de las mías son:

1. Aprender algo de Holandés.
2. Empezar a tratar mis rodillas (esto empezó hoy con @kneesovertoesguy).
3. Mejorar en el piano y la guitarra, dedicarle más tiempo. 
4. Madrugar más (Sufro con esto).
5. Comer menos azúcar. 
Entre otros 15 ¿Los tuyos?
.
.
🇬🇧 I've always believed in the power of manifesting/declaring the goals or changes you want in your life. Add a plan to that and things will happen. This year was a big one for me. Writing Scribbles, moving to Europe, reading more and getting my purple belt in jiujitsu were things I declared I wanted to do this year and I did. But I got to be honest, there are many more I couldn't do, either for lack of time or dedication. But that's ok, that's part of the process.

I want us to declare together the goals or changes we want for 2023. What are yours? And in case you need a reminder (we all often do) you can come back to this post and get it. 

Some of mine are:
1. Learn some Dutch.
2. Treat my knees (Starting the program today with @kneesovertoesguy)
3. Get better at playing the piano and the guitar.
4. Wake up earlier every morning (tough one for me).
5. Eat less sugar. 

Plus another 15 or so, what are yours?
.
.
#instagood #purpose #motivation #love #picoftheday #instalike #photooftheday #beautiful #life #change

🇬🇧 We're finally entering an exciting time where A. I will help us create and automate a lot of the tasks that took too much time, money and specialisation in the past. Generative A. I models are the foundation of this new wave of image, text and video that we're seeing everywhere and remember, this won't replace us; it will assist us.

Here's a list of my top 10 favourite A.I and automation tools:

1. Synthesia - The video below was created on it. It uses A.I avatars to produce videos in almost every language (and even accents) out there. https://www.synthesia.io/
2. Midjourney - Uses deep learning models to generate digital images from natural language descriptions. https://midjourney.com/
3. DALL:E OpenAI - Similar to Midjourney. https://openai.com/dall-e-2/
4. Craiyon - A mini DALL:E https://www.craiyon.com/
5. ChatGPT - OpenAI Chatbot pre-trained to answer pretty much any question or write anything you ask it to. https://chat.openai.com/
6. AIVA - Music generation - Deep learning algorithm fed with thousands or human compositions to create new ones. You own the rights of your creations. https://www.aiva.ai/
7. Copy.ai - Write compelling social media posts, blogs, email, etc. https://www.copy.ai/
8. Copysmith.ai - Similar to copy.ai 
9. Upword.ai - Summarises your reports/documents helping you read ten times faster, also helps you create your own.
10. Designs.ai - A.I tool to create, edit and scale content. https://designs.ai/

And if you don't have your copy of Scribbles yet, follow the A.I lady's advice and go to bookofscribbles.com 

.
.

🇪🇸 En este nuevo año tengo una sola palabra en mente, esa palabra va a definir todo lo que haga y deje de hacer, nuevos hábitos y cambios. Pero sobre todo espero que sea mi herramienta principal. 

Nunca le he apostado a esa palabra, siempre le he sido esquivo. Pero la verdad ya me cansé de huirle, de escondérmele, de temerle... Esa palabra es PRODUCTIVIDAD. 

Este año quiero ser más productivo, aprovechar más el tiempo, ver más lugares, entrenar más, escribir más, enseñar más, crear más. Pero sobre todo aprender más.

Dicho eso, este año quiero enseñar y compartir más, tal como lo hacía antes. Sé que algunos de Uds. están siempre dispuestos a escucharme y yo voy a estar más dispuesto a compartir también. El próximo martes 10 de Enero arrancamos con nuevas sesiones. Vamos a hablar de Inteligencia Artificial Generativa, sus aplicaciones y tendencias digitales para 2023.

Sólo hay 30 cupos disponibles, si quieres atender comenta esta publicación o envíame un mensaje directo y te paso el link.

Ahí nos vemos! 🤙
.
.
In this new year I have a word in mind, that word will define everything I do and stop doing, new habits and changes. But above all I hope it will be my main tool. I have never bet on that word, I've been elusive to it. 

But the truth is I'm tired of running away from it... That word is PRODUCTIVITY. This year I want to be more productive, make the most of my time, see more places, train more, write more, teach more, create more. But above all learn more.

What's your word for 2023? 
.
.

🇬🇧 RIP, my brother. 

I'm going to share a story with you, nobody actually knows this, but when I finished high school, I went into med school, don't ask me why but I didn't like any of it, and as time went by I was feeling more lost and sad about my decision, but I didn't want to disappoint my family by quitting. During that time a good friend of mine, Oscar (good looking fella on the pic) was finishing his career in advertising and he'd always talk to me about his campaigns, briefs, ideas and strategies and I found it fascinating, he was always so passionate about that stuff. One day I decided to quit med school and told him "I want to do what you do" and he helped me get into his University, helped me through the process and the rest is history. The dude became a rockstar producer and I became a digital/data ad man.

About 3 weeks ago I announced a class about 2023 trends and Generative AI and he messaged me saying "I want to learn that stuff, can I join?" I said, "Of course, see you there, man!" and a couple of days later, he died of a heart attack, how unfair is that? That friend that's invincible, strong, charming, inspiring... just like that, gone.

That dude came to say goodbye to me once at midnight when I was leaving Colombia to South Africa a couple of years back, that dude always remembered my birthday (Facebook prob helped him), and that dude always said "I love you" at the end of all of our chats, which I found a weird cause that's an odd thing to say to a male friend right? No! Love you too brother and I'll see you on the other side. 

Thanks for the inspiration and friendship.
.
.

🇪🇸 Desde niño he jugado al fútbol en la posición más difícil de todas, la portería. He jugado en el barrio con amigos, torneos con desconocidos y he competido a nivel nacional, ganando algunos partidos y perdiendo otros. Sin embargo, recientemente, jugando con jóvenes de veintitantos, he empezado a sentirme lento, viejo y sin reacción, especialmente con dolor en la espalda y las rodillas. A pesar de hacer ejercicio diariamente y comer medianamente bien, mi cuerpo ya no funciona igual. Atajar un partido de casi dos horas me deja adolorido durante una semana, y justo después de que el dolor desaparezca, hay que jugar de nuevo. Acepto que estamos envejeciendo y que ya no puedo recuperarme tan rápido como antes. Pero no voy a dejar de jugar, a pesar de vivir adolorido, porque me hace feliz. No hay moraleja en esta historia, solo que, supongo, todos envejecemos sin importar cuán atléticos o “saludables” seamos. El tiempo es implacable, por lo que debemos aprovecharlo, vivir con algo de dolor, pero felices. ¡Que tengan todos una buena noche!
.
.
🇬🇧 🇺🇸 Since I was a child, I have played soccer in the toughest position of all, the goal. I played in the neighborhood with friends, tournaments with strangers, and competed nationally, winning some games and losing others. But only now, almost at 40 years old (playing with guys in their twenties), have I started to feel slow, old, unresponsive, and especially with pain in my back and knees. Despite exercising almost daily and eating moderately well, my body no longer functions the same. Saving a match of almost two hours leaves me sore for a week, and exactly seven days later, when the pain subsides, I have to play again. I never experienced this before, even when I had serious injuries, I recovered and kept going, but now I don’t recover, everything hurts, and we have to accept that we are aging. But I’m not going to stop playing, even though I live in pain, I’m happy, so we continue ⚽️. There’s no moral to the story, only that, I guess, we all reach our time, no matter how athletic or “healthy” we are, time is brutal, and we have to take advantage of it, live with some pain but happy.

Good evening, everyone.

Great piece of work by @180amsterdam 👇

🇬🇧 Today marks #WorldPressFreedomDay, a day to celebrate the crucial role of journalism and freedom of expression as a driver for human rights. However, with a record number of journalists imprisoned around the world, press freedom is under attack. There have never been more journalists imprisoned than today.

A problem that is largely invisible. Because we can’t read what is never published.

Together with @freepressunltd we launched the Erased font. A font that aims to make the rising censorship in the world visible. The font erases a word for every journalist imprisoned, based on the topics they reported on.

Visit erased.freepressunlimited.org, to read about journalists being erased and what you, as an organization or individual, can do to help spread censorship awareness.
.
.
🇪🇸 Hoy se celebra el #DíaMundialDeLaLibertadDePrensa, un día para celebrar el papel crucial del periodismo y la libertad de expresión como motor de los derechos humanos. Sin embargo, con un número récord de periodistas encarcelados en todo el mundo, la libertad de prensa está bajo ataque. Nunca ha habido más periodistas encarcelados que hoy.

Un problema que en gran medida es invisible. Porque no podemos leer lo que nunca se publica.

Junto con @freepressunltd, lanzamos la fuente Erased (Borrada). Una fuente que busca visibilizar la creciente censura en el mundo. La fuente borra una palabra por cada periodista encarcelado, basándose en los temas sobre los que informaron.

Visita erased.freepressunlimited.org para leer sobre los periodistas que están siendo borrados y lo que tú, como organización o individuo, puedes hacer para ayudar a difundir la concienciación sobre la censura.
.
.
